Defendant Tyler Lee Johnson in court with attorney Victoria Mccandless.  Defendant Tyler Lee Johnson in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared on behalf of DeAnn L. Heard for the State of Wisconsin.   Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.  Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 6 years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2-1/2 years  with credit for  days time served.  Defendant shall serve 3-1/2 years  on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharge, plus costs and disbursements, to be taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance to be paid while on Extended Supervision.

CONDITIIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No contact with Wal Mart at 222 North Chicago Avenue, South Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - No contact with Lorelei H.;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Obtain high school diploma, HSED or GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - No driving without a valid driver's license or valid occupational license;
 - Pay any balances remaining of the costs, surcharges and disbursements as ordered.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
